	(gr_text "Question/notes/remarks:\n- no clue if test point jumper wires are big enough for the power we need ( i think it should be fine)\n- according  to the internet (pcb layout for bucks article), the gnds of Cout and Cin should is recommended to be 1-2 cm apart bc noise propagation\n- move the bst cap close to ic as well\n- fix ground\n- minimizing fb crosstalk by fb trace being far away from gnd\n- don't think C1 needs to be as close to ic bc not for decoupling"
